# Infinite Vision — Content & Program Model

## Tone & framing
- Veteran-centered, trauma-informed, dignified, mission-driven
- Memphis-specific; no hype, slang, or emojis
- No photos unless explicitly requested

## Service pillars (always align content)
1. **Housing Pathways** — Intake → Assessment → Placement → Stabilization → Case Management
2. **Transportation Hybrid Model** — priorities, Tier 1/2/3, routing, cost management, tech/coordination
3. **Financial Empowerment** — budgeting, credit, savings milestones, coaching, platform elements
4. **Community Integration** — workforce, nonprofits, faith-based (preference-based), veteran-serving orgs

## Care-model inspiration (principles only, no branding copy)
- **Foxbridge**: warm, belonging, dignity, home-like clarity
- **American House**: clean structure, professional, funder-ready modularity

## Partner ecosystem
- Include Memphis-aligned partners per Super Master Prompt; **never** include Alpha Omega Veterans Services
- Full lists: `/partners`; program pages use **collapsed** partner sections at bottom only
- No logos unless requested; text-only lists with short role descriptions
- Do not place partner sections on homepage hero, donate page, or crisis content

## De-duplication
- **Homepage**: high-level pathways and CTAs
- **Programs** (`/programs/*`): program-specific detail
- **Operations** (`/operations`): staffing, outcomes, compliance (single source of truth)
- **Partners** (`/partners`): full ecosystem

## Donations
- Replace **"Donate Online"** with official Infinite Vision PayPal embed only (never invent embed code)
- **Never** route donations through Reset Supply Co.; all donations go to Infinite Vision
